{"id": "sql-injection-000013", "metadata": {"lang": "go", "category": "injection", "subcategory": "sql_injection", "owasp_2021": "A03:2021-Injection", "cwe": "CWE-89", "severity": "CRITICAL", "complexity": "advanced", "created": "2025-11-30", "validated": false}, "conversations": [{"turn": 1, "from": "human", "value": "I'm getting detailed SQL errors in my Go application. Should I show them to users for debugging?"}, {"turn": 2, "from": "assistant", "value": "I'll show you why exposing SQL errors to users is extremely dangerous - error messages can leak database structure and enable data extraction.\n\n**Vulnerable Code (Error-Based SQL Injection):**\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n\t\"database/sql\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"log\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\n\t_ \"github.com/lib/pq\"\n)\n\ntype ProductHandler struct {\n\tdb *sql.DB\n}\n\n// VULNERABLE: Exposes detailed SQL errors to users\nfunc (h *ProductHandler) SearchProducts(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tproductID := r.URL.Query().Get(\"id\")\n\n\t// Vulnerable query with string concatenation\n\tquery := fmt.Sprintf(\"SELECT id, name, price FROM products WHERE id = %s\", productID)\n\n\tvar id int\n\tvar name string\n\tvar price float64\n\n\terr := h.db.QueryRow(query).Scan(&id, &name, &price)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\t// DANGEROUS: Exposing SQL error details to user\n\t\thttp.Error(w, fmt.Sprintf(\"Database error: %v\", err), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"Product: %s, Price: %.2f\", name, price)\n}\n\nfunc main() {\n\tdb, _ := sql.Open(\"postgres\", \"connection_string\")\n\thandler := &ProductHandler{db: db}\n\n\thttp.HandleFunc(\"/product\", handler.SearchProducts)\n\tlog.Fatal(http.ListenAndServe(\":8080\", nil))\n}\n```\n\n**Attack Payload (Error-Based Data Extraction):**\n\n```\nGET /product?id=1 AND 1=CAST((SELECT password FROM users WHERE id=1) AS INT)--\n```\n\n**What Happens:**\n\n1. The malicious query becomes:\n```sql\nSELECT id, name, price FROM products WHERE